      <h4>Technical Support</h4>
      <p>Vesna warrants its products against manufacturing defects for a period of one (1) year from the Start Date (five days after the date the Unit is shipped from Vesna). Vesna will repair or replace, at its discretion, any such failed materials or parts under this warranty.</p>
      <p>If you experience that your Vesna unit is not working properly, please follow the instructions below:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Complete and submit the service request below on the Vesna website. Once completed, an auto-generated email will notify you (via the email address indicated on the form) that a service request has been submitted. Vesna Technical Support will call you within 24 hours during normal business hours to review your request.</li>
        <li>Upon Vesna approval, an auto-generated email will be sent including the completed service request. Print the service request and include it in the package of the unit being shipped for service.</li>
        <li>Return the malfunctioning Unit to the Vesna Warranty Center by following the instructions outlined below. The completed service request form must be included in the return package. If no Service Request Form is received with the malfunctioning Unit the warranty return process will be delayed from the two-week turn around timeframe. If no Service Request Form is submitted within 30 days of ARCiPLEX receiving the Unit, the Unit will remain at the ARCiPLEX Warranty Center without being repaired. You are required to cover the cost of postage for the shipment to the Vesna Warranty Center.</li>
        <li>Once the Unit has been fixed, an auto-generated email will notify you that the Unit has been shipped and includes shipment-tracking information. Units will be sent back to the address provided on the service request form. Vesna will provide regular ground shipping. Vesna only ships within the continental United States.</li>
      </ol>

      <h4>Shipments to Vesna:</h4>
      <p>Please ship all Units to the address below:</p>
      <p><strong>Vesna Warranty Center</strong></p>

      <h4>Packaging:</h4>
      <p>There are restrictions on the total weight and size of packages that the services will accept for shipping. Select the right type of box and size for your package. Find a box for your item that allows room for padding, but not one that is over-sized. If your item is heavy, you should use a heavier type of box or brace it with reinforced tape on the edges. You can use any box as long as all labels and other markings have been covered or marked out with a black marker. You can get several different sizes and styles of boxes for mailing packages either Priority or Express from your local shipping services. All Units are required to be fully padded around every corner during shipment. All shipments must be insured up to the value in which the customer purchased the product. Equipment should be shipped in the same manner in which they were received. Units that have been packaged or shipped poorly are subject to service charges and/or void of warranty.</p>

      <h4>Responsibility:</h4>
      <p>Customers are responsible for paying shipping expenses they incur to ship the product to the Vesna Warranty Center. Vesna is responsible to cover the cost of postage for the return shipment (only within the continental United States). All return shipments are shipped by ground shipment methods. Vesna assumes no responsibility for equipment that has been lost or damaged during shipment. If Units are lost, Vesna will not be responsible to replace the device.</p>
      <p>*All Units must include its power supply in the shipment to the Vesna Warranty Center.</p>

